Global Mesophilic Dairy Starter Market Insights
Mesophilic Dairy Starter Market size was valued at USD 1.50 Billion in 2022 and is projected to reach USD 2.50 Billion by 2030, growing at a CAGR of 7.5% from 2024 to 2030.

Mesophilic Dairy Starter Market Overview
The Mesophilic Dairy Starter market is witnessing significant growth, with a valuation of approximately USD 2.1 billion in 2024. The market's expansion is driven by the increasing demand for dairy products, such as cheese, yogurt, and butter, globally. This demand is largely attributed to the rising consumption of probiotic-rich foods and the growth of dairy processing industries. Additionally, advancements in fermentation technology and the expanding awareness of the health benefits associated with mesophilic cultures are key factors contributing to market growth. As per forecasts, the Mesophilic Dairy Starter market is expected to maintain a steady compound annual growth rate (CAGR) of 6.2% from 2024 to 2030. Furthermore, North America and Europe remain key regions for market growth due to the high consumption of dairy products, while the Asia-Pacific region is projected to witness the fastest growth rate due to an increasing shift towards dairy consumption in emerging economies.

